+   is fully concrete and zero symbolic bytes reach the lexer; data file B
+   stays symbolic for the interpreter. One bitcode build, one KLEE run, one
+   manifest.json covering all menu entries -- never a cross-run merge.
+   Round 2 extends the round-1 menu (50 entries) with 40 more targeting the
+   uncovered builtins (bit ops and/or/xor/compl/lshift/rshift, strtonum,
+   typeof/isarray/mkbool, systime/strftime/mktime, system/fflush, gensub,
+   match-into-array) and io.c redirection paths (print>file, cmd|getline,
+   getline<file, print|cmd, close), plus more printf format / regex / array
